# Python 3.9 Compatibility

The ChoreBoy FreeCAD AppRun runtime ships **Python 3.9.2**. All application code, vendored libraries, and tests must run on Python 3.9.

## Prohibited (3.10+)

- `match` / `case` statements (3.10)
- `X | Y` union syntax in type annotations at runtime (3.10) — use `Union[X, Y]` or guard with `from __future__ import annotations`
- `ParamSpec`, `TypeAlias` from `typing` (3.10) — import from `typing_extensions` if needed
- `ExceptionGroup` / `except*` (3.11)
- `tomllib` (3.11) — use `tomli` vendored or avoid TOML parsing
- `TaskGroup` from `asyncio` (3.11)
- `type` keyword aliases (3.12)

## Safe to use (available in 3.9)

- Built-in generics in annotations: `list[int]`, `dict[str, int]`, `tuple[str, ...]` (PEP 585)
- `str.removeprefix()` / `str.removesuffix()`
- `zoneinfo` module
- Walrus operator `:=` (3.8+)
- f-strings (3.6+)

## Guidance

- When unsure about annotation compatibility, add `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of the module.
- Before adding a new dependency, verify it still publishes wheels or pure-Python packages supporting Python 3.9.
